# Handoff Documentation Rules

## For AI Agent

### When to Create Handoff Documents

- When a task requires multiple AI sessions to complete
- When refactoring or optimization work spans multiple files/modules
- When the user explicitly requests handoff documentation
- When the AI determines that follow-up work will be needed
- When complex changes affect multiple parts of the codebase

### Document Structure

Create handoff documents in `.cursor/mockdowns/` directory with the following naming format:
`[INDEX]_[BRIEF_DESCRIPTION]_[DATE].md`

Where:

- `INDEX`: Sequential number (01, 02, 03, ...)
- `BRIEF_DESCRIPTION`: Short description of the work (in Korean, lowercase with hyphens)
- `DATE`: Date in YYYYMMDD format

Example: `01_vnode-normalization-refactor_20250115.md`

